LANDECK, Austria (AP) -- Austrian soldiers took advantage of a  break in heavy snowfall today to mount a rescue of avalanche victims from a stricken Alpine town, joining villagers who dug with their bare hands in a frantic effort to reach those buried below.
AT LEAST 17 DEAD, MORE MISSING IN AUSTRIAN AVALANCHES
Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT February 24
VIENNA -- At least eight people have been confirmed killed and30 others injured as two avalanches roared through a ski resort inAustria's western state of Triol on Tuesday evening, the Austriannews media reported.
